		<description><![CDATA[Spin-a-Wind 2.0 is now available on iTunes.  The update addressed a suggestion from a user in Germany who wanted a graphical representation of the runway and wind direction.  Also, after talking with other airlines pilots, it seemed like a no-brainer to add another page with a temperature conversion from Celsius to Fahrenheit.  [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Spin-a-Wind 2.0 is now available on iTunes.  The update addressed a suggestion from a user in Germany who wanted a graphical representation of the runway and wind direction.  Also, after talking with other airlines pilots, it seemed like a no-brainer to add another page with a temperature conversion from Celsius to Fahrenheit.  And, since I had some leftover screen real estate, I employed the somewhat complicated wind-chill formula used by the U.S. National Weather Service and Canada.<br />
It works with all versions of the iPhone and iPod Touch, and probably the new iPad.  It doesn&#8217;t need an internet connection to function.  Visit <a href="http://www.spinawind.com">The Spin-a-Wind Site.</a></p>
<p>Here are some screen shots:</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td>
<div id="attachment_96" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 210px"><img src="http://flyingpilot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/img_0013-200x300.png" alt="Spin-a-Wind" title="Spin-a-Wind Main Page" width="200" height="300" class="size-medium wp-image-96" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Spin-a-Wind</p></div>
</td>
<td>
<div id="attachment_97" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 210px"><img src="http://flyingpilot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/img_0014-200x300.png" alt="Spin-a-Temp" title="Spin-a-Temp Temperature Converter" width="200" height="300" class="size-medium wp-image-97" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Spin-a-Temp</p></div></td>
</tr>
</table>
]]></content:encoded>
